tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE return_rates_analysis (
  return_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  product_id INT,
  return_reason TEXT,
  return_date DATE,
  customer_id INT,
  satisfaction_rating INT
);

CREATE TABLE returns (
    return_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT,
    product_id INT,
    return_date DATE,
    return_reason VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE products (
    product_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_name VARCHAR(255),
    category VARCHAR(50),
    price DECIMAL(10, 2),
    avg_return_rate DECIMAL(5, 2)
);

CREATE TABLE Returns (
   return_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   customer_id INT,
   order_id INT,
   return_date DATE,
   return_reason TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE Products (
   product_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   product_name TEXT,
   category TEXT,
   price DECIMAL,
   stock_quantity INT
);

CREATE TABLE Customers (
   customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   customer_name TEXT,
   email TEXT,
   phone_number TEXT,
   address TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE returns (
   return_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   product_id INT,
   customer_id INT,
   return_date DATE,
   return_reason TEXT,
   FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id),
   FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id)
);

CREATE TABLE feedback (
   feedback_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   customer_id INT,
   feedback_text TEXT,
   feedback_date TIMESTAMP,
   stars INT,
   FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id)
);
CREATE TABLE Returns (return_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_id INT, order_id INT, return_reason TEXT, return_date DATE)
CREATE TABLE Customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name TEXT, email TEXT, phone_number TEXT)
CREATE TABLE Orders (order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_id INT, order_date DATE, total_amount DECIMAL(10,2), status TEXT)
CREATE TABLE Products (product_id INT PRIMARY KEY, product_name TEXT, category TEXT, price DECIMAL(8,2), stock_quantity INT)
CREATE TABLE ReturnsHistory (return_id INT, customer_id INT, order_id INT, return_reason TEXT, return_date DATE, resolution TEXT)
